Invocable Method: - Apex method which decalared @InvocableMethod anotation to call this from flow and pass the data.

    To make a method "Invocable" you must follow these strict rules: - 
                        1). Annotation Must use @InvocableMethod.
                        2). Method must be static.
                        3). Method can be a public or global.
                        4). It can only take one input parameter.
                        5). Parameter must be a List.
                        6). It must return either void or a List.
                        7). we can only have one @InvocableMethod in a single Apex class.


    Inside the @InvocableMethod parentheses, you can define: - 
                                                              1). label: What the user sees in the Flow Builder search.
                                                              2). description: Explains what the action does.

    Syntax with Example: - 
                        @InvocableMethod(label='calling apex method from flow ' description='Receives a string and performs logic')
                            public static void receiveString(List<String> inputStrings) {
                                // Salesforce sends a list; loop through it to get your value
                                for (String str : inputStrings) {
                                    System.debug('Received string from Flow: ' + str);
                                    
                                    // Your custom logic goes here (e.g., updating a record, calling an API)
                                }
                            }
